// Negative fixture (issue #45): a phase cycle. Three rules each read a
// different relation `without` (Appendix E: `without` reads are strict —
// they must be fully settled before the rule fires) in a ring: A negates
// RC, B negates RA, C negates RB. Every `without` witness variable is
// separately bound by `Seed`, so this is not a name-resolution/absence-
// witness failure — it is a genuine non-monotone cycle across three phase
// components (RA -> RB -> RC -> RA), which phase assignment must reject
// deterministically with BRX4001 rather than silently picking an
// (unsound) evaluation order.
package neg.cycle @ 0.1.0

rel Seed { x: I64 } key(x)
rel RA { x: I64 } key(x)
rel RB { x: I64 } key(x)
rel RC { x: I64 } key(x)

derive A: RA(x: x) from {
  Seed(x: x)
  without { RC(x: x) }
}

derive B: RB(x: x) from {
  Seed(x: x)
  without { RA(x: x) }
}

derive C: RC(x: x) from {
  Seed(x: x)
  without { RB(x: x) }
}
